</math></div><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/03270d84a865fef1d99d97a486741843c7232d07" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-display" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:63.236ex; height:3.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle W_{m}=\operatorname {span} (\psi _{m,n}:n\in \mathbb {Z} ),{\text{ where }}\psi _{m,n}(t)=2^{-m/2}\psi (2^{-m}t-n).}"></div>
The father wavelet <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle V_{i}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <msub>
          <mi>V</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>i</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle V_{i}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f300b83673e961a9d48f3862216b167f94e5668c" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.155ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="V_{i}"></span> keeps the time domain properties, while the mother wavelets <span class="mwe-math-element"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle W_{i}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
