</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/716fde9365cf372e6a39b87b3cd21936b78ac330" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:20.992ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \dots ,W_{1},W_{0},W_{-1},\dots }"></span> are the orthogonal "differences" of the above sequence, that is, <i>W<sub>m</sub></i> is the orthogonal complement of <i>V<sub>m</sub></i> inside the subspace <i>V</i><sub><i>m</i>−1</sub>,
<div class="mwe-math-element"><div class="mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math display="block" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle V_{m}\oplus W_{m}=V_{m-1}.}">
